
Email Service Application

Overview
This project is an email service application built with React.js and JavaScript. The application includes functionalities such as retry mechanisms, fallback between providers, idempotency, rate limiting, and status tracking.

Key Features
Retry Mechanism: Automatically retries sending emails with exponential backoff in case of failures.
Fallback Between Providers: Uses a secondary email provider if the primary provider fails.
Idempotency: Ensures that emails with the same unique ID are not sent more than once.
Rate Limiting: Prevents sending too many emails in a short period.
Status Tracking: Logs the status of each email send attempt, including success, failure, and retry attempts.

Technology Stack
Frontend: React.js
Backend: JavaScript (Node.js)
CSS: Standard CSS for styling

Prerequisites
Node.js (for running the development server and building the project)
npm (Node Package Manager)

to run this project : 
npm install

to run the project :
npm start 